This paper is about federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a new algorithm for federated learning that improves upon the standard Federated Averaging algorithm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses control theory, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) may be a relevant category. Finally, the paper mentions computer vision applications, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) may also be a relevant category.
